your biggest concern right now?

256
00:28:53,110 --> 00:28:54,278
What about you, then?

257
00:28:54,820 --> 00:28:57,948
You're worried your dad will
scold you, in front of a cancer patient?

258
00:29:06,581 --> 00:29:07,833
It's not that big a deal.

259
00:29:16,883 --> 00:29:17,884
You're here?

260
00:29:18,385 --> 00:29:20,470
Looks like you partied hard tonight, too.

261
00:29:27,894 --> 00:29:28,854
See you tomorrow.

262
00:29:28,937 --> 00:29:30,856
Thank you, get home safe.

263
00:29:34,776 --> 00:29:37,404
Take the glitter off your face at least.

264
00:29:38,155 --> 00:29:39,489
Gosh, you reek of alcohol.

265
00:30:01,845 --> 00:30:03,347
Get up already!

266
00:30:07,059 --> 00:30:08,518
Aren't you going to work?

267
00:30:36,630 --> 00:30:37,839
Why aren't you washing up?

268
00:31:05,992 --> 00:31:08,954
What an idiot. Gosh.

269
00:31:09,037 --> 00:31:11,623
Be quiet. I'm already annoyed.

270
00:31:12,707 --> 00:31:13,959
When will you tell them?

271
00:31:14,042 --> 00:31:16,253
-I will.
-When?

272
00:31:16,336 --> 00:31:17,504
For God's sake…

273
00:31:23,093 --> 00:31:25,679
-Mom, this brat quit his job!
-Hey!

274
00:31:31,768 --> 00:31:34,020
SANPO SINKS

275
00:31:34,980 --> 00:31:35,814
Damn it!

276
00:31:57,335 --> 00:31:59,337
People are waiting.

277
00:32:00,005 --> 00:32:01,965
Let's talk to him after we're done.

278
00:32:21,276 --> 00:32:23,612
I don't know anymore.
I'll be dead meat later.

279
00:32:53,975 --> 00:32:55,727
<i>Whenever I wanted to quit,</i>

280
00:32:57,187 --> 00:32:59,439
I'd think,
"Maybe after the summer vacation."

281
00:33:00,148 --> 00:33:02,901
"Maybe after Chuseok."

282
00:33:03,485 --> 00:33:04,486
Then I'd think,

283
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:07,405
"I'll be lonely at the end of the year."

284
00:33:08,073 --> 00:33:09,783
"And working isn't so bad in spring."

285
00:33:10,659 --> 00:33:12,452
And another year would go by.

286
00:33:13,078 --> 00:33:13,995
I mean,

287
00:33:14,496 --> 00:33:19,084
I'm not like A-reum, a greedy workaholic
whose only goal is making money.

288
00:33:20,210 --> 00:33:21,878
I think I've come

289
00:33:23,630 --> 00:33:25,131
far enough.

290
00:33:26,550 --> 00:33:28,093
This isn't the right path for me.

291
00:33:28,843 --> 00:33:31,221
I don't have to force myself
to keep walking on it.

292
00:33:33,515 --> 00:33:35,559
You don't need to explain yourself to me.

293
00:33:36,142 --> 00:33:37,352
As if I don't understand.

294
00:33:44,568 --> 00:33:46,069
To tell you the truth,

295
00:33:47,112 --> 00:33:49,239
I don't have a specific goal in my life.

296
00:33:50,532 --> 00:33:53,118
Money, women, honor… Nothing.

297
00:33:54,619 --> 00:33:55,537
But…

298
00:33:56,580 --> 00:33:57,622
do I…

299
00:33:59,249 --> 00:34:01,167
have to have a goal?

300
00:34:01,835 --> 00:34:04,170
Can't I just live my life without one?

301
00:34:05,255 --> 00:34:09,175
I can't force myself to live
for something I don't really desire.

302
00:34:18,310 --> 00:34:20,353
<i>I wish I had an older brother.</i>

303
00:34:21,062 --> 00:34:23,857
<i>Then I would be able to live as I wished.</i>

304
00:34:25,692 --> 00:34:27,402
<i>He doesn't exist,</i>

305
00:34:28,236 --> 00:34:29,571
<i>but I miss him.</i>

306
00:34:46,046 --> 00:34:47,839
Did someone die or something?

307
00:34:50,008 --> 00:34:52,886
He's worked at that company
for eight years. That's enough.

308
00:34:52,969 --> 00:34:55,513
It's hard to get a job somewhere else
after you turn 40.

309
00:34:55,597 --> 00:34:57,807
The younger you are, the better.

310
00:34:57,891 --> 00:35:01,603
Young people these days
move from one job to another really often.

311
00:35:04,189 --> 00:35:07,484
Staying at the same job for long
isn't considered a virtue anymore.

312
00:35:07,567 --> 00:35:11,071
How do you know what suits you better?
You have to try different workplaces.

313
00:35:22,207 --> 00:35:23,208
So?

314
00:35:24,209 --> 00:35:26,252
What's your plan?

315
00:35:30,715 --> 00:35:33,927
I'm not going to do anything
for a little while.

316
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:37,639
How long is a little while?

317
00:35:44,688 --> 00:35:45,605
Dad…

318
00:35:48,566 --> 00:35:51,611
Can't you treat me
even half as well as you treated Gu?

319
00:35:53,238 --> 00:35:54,447
You'd worry about Gu

320
00:35:54,531 --> 00:35:58,910
if you hadn't seen him in a while.
"Is he sick? Did he eat?" But to me…

321
00:36:13,049 --> 00:36:15,677
I know I'm not a perfect son or anything.

322
00:36:16,845 --> 00:36:19,139
But I haven't done
anything I'm ashamed of.

323
00:36:19,723 --> 00:36:22,100
There are so many bad people out there,

324
00:36:22,183 --> 00:36:25,478
but I've never done anything
to be an embarrassment to you.

325
00:36:26,187 --> 00:36:29,691
The thing I brought home the other day.
I said it was from the company,

326
00:36:29,774 --> 00:36:32,360
but it was from the store owners
who heard I was quitting.

327
00:36:33,153 --> 00:36:36,781
There are even people who promised
to gift me 500,000 won when I get married.

328
00:36:36,865 --> 00:36:39,701
But do you think
they were all nice from the beginning?

329
00:36:39,784 --> 00:36:41,828
No, I had to work really hard!

330
00:36:42,912 --> 00:36:45,665
You work with machines.
You don't have to talk to anyone,

331
00:36:45,749 --> 00:36:48,334
so you have no idea
what it's like to work with people.

332
00:36:49,335 --> 00:36:52,547
But I still never lost my temper
or got myself into trouble.

333
00:36:52,630 --> 00:36:55,633
They even gave me gifts.
That should be enough!

334
00:36:56,634 --> 00:36:59,471
It's not like I'm going
to idle away for the rest of my life!

335
00:37:04,684 --> 00:37:06,478
"You've worked really hard."

336
00:37:07,187 --> 00:37:08,313
"Take a break."

337
00:37:09,355 --> 00:37:10,899
Can't you just say that?

338
00:39:46,220 --> 00:39:48,181
It's huge!

339
00:39:48,264 --> 00:39:49,140
Look at this.

340
00:39:49,223 --> 00:39:51,267
-Amazing!
-Check this one out!

341
00:39:51,351 --> 00:39:52,310
-Mom.
-Dad,

342
00:39:52,393 --> 00:39:53,353
-What?
-look at this.

343
00:39:53,895 --> 00:39:56,064
What's that? Hey, wait. Stay there.

344
00:39:56,147 --> 00:39:57,106
Oh, my God.

345
00:39:57,190 --> 00:39:58,942
Hey, take a picture of us.

346
00:39:59,025 --> 00:40:00,109
Mom, look.

347
00:40:01,194 --> 00:40:02,070
Look this way.

348
00:40:03,029 --> 00:40:05,323
One, two, three.

349
00:40:05,823 --> 00:40:07,700
Let's take a group picture.

350
00:40:07,784 --> 00:40:09,410
-Shall we?
-Yes.

351
00:40:09,994 --> 00:40:11,746
One, two, three.

352
00:40:12,538 --> 00:40:14,374
One more, smile!

353
00:40:18,711 --> 00:40:19,587
Look.

354
00:40:21,339 --> 00:40:23,758
-Sweet potatoes keep coming out.
-They grew so well.

355
00:40:24,300 --> 00:40:25,677
That's odd.

356
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:28,262
It's right next to ours.
Why did theirs grow so poorly?

357
00:40:28,346 --> 00:40:29,764
-Look at this.
-Gosh.

358
00:40:29,847 --> 00:40:32,767
Just because you farmed for long
doesn't mean you're good at it.

359
00:40:32,850 --> 00:40:35,061
You need to learn the know-how.

360
00:40:35,645 --> 00:40:36,479
Exactly.

361
00:40:36,562 --> 00:40:39,857
These days, it's easy to learn things

362
00:40:39,941 --> 00:40:42,402
-Yes.
-Goodness, we'll be rich.

363
00:40:43,528 --> 00:40:44,904
All right.

364
00:40:46,030 --> 00:40:49,200
-Dad, this is seriously awesome.
-There's more here. Good.

365
00:40:49,283 --> 00:40:51,160
-Take a picture.
-One, two, three.

366
00:40:51,869 --> 00:40:53,705
These are seriously huge!

367
00:41:36,205 --> 00:41:37,206
Don't!

368
00:41:46,174 --> 00:41:47,759
How dare they…

369
00:41:50,970 --> 00:41:52,472
Fine, let's do it.

370
00:42:08,654 --> 00:42:10,865
Let's go!

371
00:42:28,716 --> 00:42:29,592
Nice!

372
00:42:29,675 --> 00:42:31,677
Please, don't!

373
00:42:31,761 --> 00:42:32,887
Nice one, Dad!

374
00:42:41,771 --> 00:42:43,731
We almost caught up with them, Dad!

375
00:42:49,779 --> 00:42:50,780
Yes, let's go.

376
00:42:52,281 --> 00:42:53,574
Dad, step on it!

377
00:42:53,658 --> 00:42:54,700
Step on it, Dad!

378
00:43:32,613 --> 00:43:33,447
Dad…

379
00:43:33,531 --> 00:43:35,867
-Christ…
-My goodness.

380
00:43:36,784 --> 00:43:38,035
Be careful!

381
00:43:44,083 --> 00:43:44,959
Gosh…

382
00:43:46,294 --> 00:43:48,004
-Are you okay, Mom?
-You little…

383
00:43:48,087 --> 00:43:49,005
Hey, what…

384
00:43:49,088 --> 00:43:50,715
-You should have stopped him!
-Wait…

385
00:43:50,798 --> 00:43:52,884
-"Step on it"? You idiot!
-Hang on.

386
00:43:52,967 --> 00:43:54,594
Step on what?

387
00:43:54,677 --> 00:43:56,179
-Wait, Mom.
-Step on what?

388
00:44:00,308 --> 00:44:02,685
Are the sweet potatoes really
the priority right now?

389
00:44:07,023 --> 00:44:08,357
God, I can't believe it.

390
00:44:08,441 --> 00:44:11,110
-I can't believe it, you brat!
-Stop, Mom.

391
00:44:11,193 --> 00:44:12,361
-It hurts.
-You!

392
00:44:20,369 --> 00:44:22,121
For the love of God.

393
00:44:22,747 --> 00:44:26,250
Poor me, I have to cook
even after crashing into a rice paddy.

394
00:44:46,896 --> 00:44:48,105
Sell the field

395
00:44:48,189 --> 00:44:50,399
whether or not
you hire someone for the factory.

396
00:44:51,692 --> 00:44:53,402
Farming is too much.

397
00:44:53,486 --> 00:44:55,363
Tending the crops that grow like crazy,

398
00:44:55,446 --> 00:44:57,657
sowing and harvesting them…

399
00:44:57,740 --> 00:44:59,742
God, I can't do it anymore.

400
00:45:02,411 --> 00:45:05,289
You just eat, put down your spoon,

401
00:45:05,373 --> 00:45:07,792
and go back out to the field
or the factory.

402
00:45:07,875 --> 00:45:10,711
But I have to follow you around

403
00:45:10,795 --> 00:45:14,590
coming in and out of the house
dozens of times to cook for you.

404
00:45:15,466 --> 00:45:18,552
And it's not like I have any days off.

405
00:45:19,136 --> 00:45:21,389
It's 365 days a year.

406
00:45:22,723 --> 00:45:24,725
I had a day off
when we used to go to church.

407
00:45:25,685 --> 00:45:28,688
But you couldn't even let me have that
and stopped going.

408
00:45:28,771 --> 00:45:31,107
I'm going to start attending church again!

409
00:45:34,110 --> 00:45:36,278
Goodness, what's wrong with me?

410
00:45:36,362 --> 00:45:37,947
Why am I sweating so much?

411
00:45:44,829 --> 00:45:45,871
Did you finish work?

412
00:45:47,039 --> 00:45:48,958
Well, something suddenly came up.

413
00:45:49,917 --> 00:45:52,044
I think I'll be a bit late today.

414
00:45:52,670 --> 00:45:54,380
Then I'll go first and wait for you.

415
00:45:55,381 --> 00:45:56,465
Well…

416
00:45:56,549 --> 00:45:58,175
I think I'll be done quite late.

417
00:45:58,801 --> 00:46:01,262
If it gets too late, I can just go home.

418
00:46:01,345 --> 00:46:03,973
Don't worry about me
and focus on your work. Bye.

419
00:46:06,851 --> 00:46:10,104
On days like this, just go home early!

420
00:46:11,647 --> 00:46:13,774
You'll fall sick, dating that hard.

421
00:46:13,858 --> 00:46:15,985
How can you go
and see him every single day?

422
00:46:16,652 --> 00:46:17,903
It's close by, anyway.

423
00:46:36,964 --> 00:46:38,507
I tried imagining it.

424
00:46:40,217 --> 00:46:41,761
If I were your age

425
00:46:42,470 --> 00:46:44,638
and my dad got a girlfriend…

426
00:46:46,932 --> 00:46:48,142
I'd hate it too.

427
00:46:49,977 --> 00:46:52,271
What would that lady have to do
for me to like her?

428
00:46:53,481 --> 00:46:56,317
I'd hate it if she tried hard
to get close to me,

429
00:46:57,068 --> 00:47:00,112
and I'd hate it if she treated me
like a thorn in her side, too.

430
00:47:00,821 --> 00:47:03,824
I could reluctantly accept her

431
00:47:05,701 --> 00:47:07,661
if she were a selfless, independent woman.

432
00:47:10,915 --> 00:47:14,502
So today, I tried to look like
a selfless, independent woman,

433
00:47:14,585 --> 00:47:16,003
chattering away by myself,

434
00:47:18,839 --> 00:47:23,427
but all those words I said
to make you accept me

435
00:47:24,845 --> 00:47:27,014
didn't seem to work at all.

436
00:47:28,933 --> 00:47:30,434
So I'm a bit sad.

437
00:47:38,484 --> 00:47:39,693
I'm going to start crying.

438
00:47:47,451 --> 00:47:48,452
Hi. You're back late.

439
00:47:50,037 --> 00:47:51,413
Where's your Auntie Hui-seon?

440
00:47:51,497 --> 00:47:52,581
She went to the store.

441
00:47:52,665 --> 00:47:53,833
And left you here alone?

442
00:47:56,752 --> 00:47:57,711
What about your dad?

443
00:47:57,795 --> 00:47:59,213
He says he'll be late.

444
00:48:05,136 --> 00:48:06,470
Why are you here every day?

445
00:48:07,054 --> 00:48:08,556
Do we owe you money or something?

446
00:48:36,709 --> 00:48:37,877
I'm not leaving.

447
00:48:38,419 --> 00:48:39,879
Not until I see Tae-hun.

448
00:48:57,688 --> 00:49:01,275
Think carefully.
It's not easy to raise someone else's kid.

449
00:49:01,358 --> 00:49:03,527
Even raising my own kids
drives me up the wall.

450
00:49:04,069 --> 00:49:06,864
That's because they're your own kids.

451
00:49:06,947 --> 00:49:09,325
Do you know how much
you can hate someone else's kid?

452
00:49:13,996 --> 00:49:17,041
I didn't say we're getting married!
We're just dating!

453
00:49:17,124 --> 00:49:19,043
Goodness me, just dating?

454
00:49:19,126 --> 00:49:20,794
Once you get attached, that's it.

455
00:49:24,298 --> 00:49:25,633
For God's sake.

456
00:49:25,716 --> 00:49:28,594
I should have cut him off then and there.

457
00:49:29,220 --> 00:49:31,764
He would've found someone else to marry.

458
00:49:32,348 --> 00:49:36,727
Why did I feel sorry for him
when he looked so down?

459
00:49:36,810 --> 00:49:38,896
Now I'm his personal cook.

460
00:49:47,321 --> 00:49:50,616
I'll just stop by and take a look.

461
00:49:52,326 --> 00:49:55,287
I'll be able to tell
if he's the one for you.

462
00:49:55,371 --> 00:49:56,830
Forget it!

463
00:49:57,539 --> 00:50:00,459
I can just walk past
and take a quick look.

464
00:50:00,542 --> 00:50:01,710
Before it's too late.

465
00:50:02,294 --> 00:50:04,463
Seriously!

466
00:50:15,683 --> 00:50:17,351
-Yes,
-Thanks.

467
00:50:30,322 --> 00:50:34,201
This place used to be really small.
It seems they've expanded it.

468
00:50:34,910 --> 00:50:38,414
We used to come here a lot
when I was living with my aunt.

469
00:50:39,081 --> 00:50:41,125
I think Gyeong-seon told me.

470
00:50:41,208 --> 00:50:42,084
Really?

471
00:51:01,437 --> 00:51:03,897
I heard the <i>sujebi </i>here is really good.

472
00:51:03,981 --> 00:51:05,983
-Yes, it really is.
-I see.

473
00:51:06,066 --> 00:51:09,111
I'm reminded of how
I used to have them when I was little.

474
00:51:09,194 --> 00:51:11,864
Plus, octopus is pretty healthy, I hear.

475
00:51:11,947 --> 00:51:12,906
Yes.

476
00:51:12,990 --> 00:51:17,870
I still have the memories
of eating here when I was little.

477
00:51:18,871 --> 00:51:19,913
-I see.
-Yes.

478
00:51:28,297 --> 00:51:30,966
I ordered a seafood pancake for you, okay?

479
00:51:31,050 --> 00:51:32,885
And I paid the bill.

480
00:51:33,927 --> 00:51:35,721
Enjoy your meal.

481
00:51:36,305 --> 00:51:37,306
Okay.

482
00:51:48,484 --> 00:51:51,153
-The food's good here.
-I see.

483
00:51:52,696 --> 00:51:53,530
Who…

484
00:51:54,156 --> 00:51:56,075
Shall I order something else, too?

485
00:51:57,201 --> 00:51:59,036
No, it's fine, thank you.

486
00:52:12,216 --> 00:52:13,258
Who was that?

487
00:52:15,469 --> 00:52:17,846
-My mom.
-What? Gosh, your mother?

488
00:52:17,930 --> 00:52:19,264
No!

489
00:52:20,432 --> 00:52:23,352
Damn it, she was supposed
to act like she didn't know me.

490
00:52:35,369 --> 00:52:36,411
Hello.

491
00:52:36,995 --> 00:52:40,248
Long time no see!
Did you go somewhere today?

492
00:52:40,332 --> 00:52:43,085
Yes, to see someone.

493
00:52:43,960 --> 00:52:45,587
I heard you're selling your field.

494
00:52:45,670 --> 00:52:48,382
Yes. Gosh, I can't do it anymore.

495
00:52:48,465 --> 00:52:50,592
Of course not, at your age.

496
00:52:50,675 --> 00:52:52,636
You've got the factory
and the chores at home.

497
00:52:52,719 --> 00:52:55,847
If you marry a workaholic,
it's the woman who suffers.

498
00:52:55,931 --> 00:52:56,765
Exactly…

499
00:52:57,432 --> 00:52:58,517
Hye-suk!

500
00:52:58,600 --> 00:53:00,060
Did you find your dog?

501
00:53:00,143 --> 00:53:01,645
-Sorry?
-Your family dog.

502
00:53:01,728 --> 00:53:03,021
-Did you find it?
-What?

503
00:53:03,105 --> 00:53:05,065
When have we ever had a dog?

504
00:53:05,148 --> 00:53:06,316
What?

505
00:53:06,858 --> 00:53:09,236
A while ago, I saw Mi-jeong
crying her eyes out,

506
00:53:09,319 --> 00:53:12,239
and when I asked her what was wrong,
she said she lost her dog.

507
00:53:12,322 --> 00:53:13,782
It was about a month ago.

508
00:53:22,833 --> 00:53:25,836
-Three of these, please.
-Sure.

509
00:53:26,545 --> 00:53:29,589
If it wasn't a dog, what was it? A goat?

510
00:54:58,553 --> 00:55:00,305
Your percentage has gone up even more.

511
00:55:03,099 --> 00:55:07,187
Yeom Mi-jeong is moving in
for the final blow.

512
00:55:07,270 --> 00:55:09,856
VOTE

513
00:55:20,909 --> 00:55:23,411
YEOM MI-JEONG:
WHERE ARE YOU?

